<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<H2>
What Are Isotopes and What Can Be Learned From Them?
</H2>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
Fig. 7:  Isotope and chemical methods complement each other in
studying the Palinpinon geothermal field in the Philippines. 
Tritium and <SUP>18</SUP>O identify the incursion of cooler
"meteoric" water during exploitation.
<P>
<CENTER>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC=/worldatom/inforesource/other/gallery/fig6.gif WIDTH=350
HEIGHT=200>
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
Fig. 8:  IAEA technical assistance on isotope hydrology produced
a hydrological model of the Palinpinon field during exploitation.
The components of geothermal fluids and the processes affecting
them were determined using isotope and chemical techniques.
<P>
<CENTER>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC=/worldatom/inforesource/other/gallery/fig7.gif WIDTH=350
HEIGHT=200>
