<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Isotopes in Water and Environmental Management
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<H2>
What Are Isotopes and What Can Be Learned From Them?
</H2>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
Fig. 9:  Groundwater "ages" in the Syrian desert range up to
40,000 years.  More negative values of <SUP>2</SUP>H indicate
moister past climates with a very wet period about 10,000 to
20,000 years ago.  More positive values, also found in the Sahara
desert, indicate peristent aridity in the region.  Isotope
methods determined that the age of major groundwater reserves
beneath the Sahara is greater than 10,000 years.
<P>
<CENTER>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC=/worldatom/inforesource/other/gallery/fig8.gif WIDHT=360
HEIGHT=220>
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
</BODY>
</HTML>
