<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Isotopes in Water and Environmental Management
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<H2>
Isotopes in Water and Environmental Management
</H2>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<UL>
<LI>
<B>
Isotope Analyses:  Ensuring Quality Services through
International Support
</B>
</UL>
<P>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5>
<TR>
<TD>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC=/worldatom/inforesource/other/gallery/is4.gif>
<TD>
The IAEA isotope hydrology laboratory analyzes water
samples from Member States.  A water sample (50-500ml) is
collected
from a spring, well, faucet or from rainfall.  In the laboratory,
water samples are prepared for isotopic analysis, and stable
isotope ratios are measured with a mass spectrometer.
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC=/worldatom/inforesource/other/gallery/is5.gif>
<TD>
Field precipitation of carbonate from water samples for
<SUP>14</SUP>C analysis in the lab.  The results indicate the age
of water.
</TABLE>
<P>
