<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<H2>
Isotopes in Water and Environmental Management
</H2>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<UL>
<LI>
<B>
New Tools; New Applications; New Challenges
</B>
</UL>
<P>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5>
<TR>
<TD>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC=/worldatom/inforesource/other/gallery/is6.gif>
<TD>
A tandem particle accelerator in Switzerland.  Accelerator Mass
Spectrometry (AMS), a new and extremely sensitive technique for
the
measurement of radioactive and stable isotopes, has been
developed
at various centres around the world.  It has revolutionized
dating
techniques and quickly found applications in hydrology.
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC=/worldatom/inforesource/other/gallery/is7.gif>
<TD>
Isotope techniques can estimate the rate of sedimentation in
dams.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
