GC Resolution 39/6</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<B>GC(39)/6<BR>
28 June 1995<BR>
Item 9 of the provisional agenda</B>
<P>
<CENTER>
<H2>Election of Members to the Board of Governors</H2>
<P>
<A HREF=gc3928.html><I>See the Memorandum by the President</I></A>
<P>
</CENTER>
<HR SIZE=3>
<P>
<OL>
<LI>The Board of Governors desires to inform the General Conference that pursuant to Article VI.A.1 of the Statute it has made the following designations of members of the Agency to serve on the Board from the end of the thirty-ninth (1995) regular session to the end of the fortieth (1996) regular session of the General Conference.
<PRE>         
         
         ARGENTINA              INDIA
         AUSTRALIA              JAPAN
         BELGIUM                RUSSIAN FEDERATION
         CANADA                 SOUTH AFRICA
         CHINA                  UNITED KINGDOM OF GREAT BRITAIN
         FRANCE                 AND NORTHERN IRELAND
         GERMANY                UNITED STATES OF AMERICA
</PRE> 
<P>       
<LI>In making these designations, which include the designation of South Africa, the Board took into account General Conference resolution GC(XXXVIII)/RES/18 relating to "The participation of South Africa in the activities of the International Atomic Energy Agency" (item 8 of the provisional agenda).
<P>
<LI>One Governor expressed a reservation regarding the above designations on the grounds that they did not comply with the provisions of Article VI.A.1 of the Statute.
</OL>
