GC(39)/22
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<STRONG>
GC(39)/22<BR>
15 September 1995 <BR>
Items 6 and 30 of the provisional agenda
</STRONG>
<P>
<CENTER>
<H4>
Voluntary Contributions to the Technical Co-Operation Fund for the Year 1996
</H4>
<P>
<I>(Editor's note: The tables are not included here.)</I>
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
1. On 13 September 1995, the Board of Governors recommended a target of United States dollars 64,500,000 for voluntary contributions to the Technical Co-operation Fund for 1996.
<P>
2. The attached table shows the minimum amount each Member State would need to contribute if it wished to pledge in accordance with resolution GC(V)/RES/100 as amended by resolution GC(XV)/RES/286.
<P>         
3. Delegations are invited to communicate their Governments' pledges as soon as possible to the officer who will be sitting during plenary meetings at a table marked "Voluntary Contributions" in the Plenary Hall at the Austria Center and who will at other  times be in office A-443 on the second floor.
<P>         
4. It is foreseen that the Conference will consider the matter of voluntary contributions to the Technical Co-operation Fund under item 6 of the provisional agenda. Daily reports on voluntary contributions pledged will be issued as the session proceeds for the purpose of keeping the Conference informed of the pledges that Members are making. The total value of the pledges made as at the end of the Conference session will be communicated to the Conference by the President under item 30 of the provisional agenda.
<P>
