<TITLE>
GC(39)/24
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<STRONG>
GC(39)/24<BR>
17 September 1995<BR>
Item 14 of the provisional agenda
</STRONG>
<P>
<CENTER>
<H4>
Scale of Assessment of Members' Contributions for 1996
</H4>
<P>
<I>
(Editor's note: The tables are not included here.)
</CENTER>
</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
1. The Director General submits herewith to the General Conference a draft resolution whereby the Conference may set, in accordance with Article XIV.D of the Statute, the scale of assessment of Members' contributions to the Agency's Regular Budget for 1996. The scale annexed to the attached draft resolution has been prepared in accordance with the principles established by the General Conference (<A HREF=#FOOTNOTE_1>*</A>) and on the assumption that the Conference will approve the revised arrangements for the assessment of Members' contributions towards the Agency's Regular Budget which are the subject of document GC(39)/23/Add.2. The scale, based on the Agency's membership as of 31 July 1995, includes one new State, Yemen, which became a Member on 14 October 1994.
<P>
2. With regard to the scale annexed to the attached draft resolution, on the basis of the revised principles set forth in document GC(39)/23/Add.2 the Director General has drawn up a list of Members meeting the criteria laid down there for partial relief in respect of their assessments of the safeguards component of the Regular Budget. The list comprises 91 Members (see Table 2 in the Appendix). The remaining 31 Members will contribute on a proportionally increased basis in order to make up the balance of the safeguards expenses.
<P>
3. It will be noted that the following draft resolution also provides for approval by the General Conference of the base rate of assessment of each Member. This has been derived from the scale used by the United Nations to assess contributions from its Members to its Regular Budget for 1995 and adopted by the General Assembly in resolution 49/19 B on 29 November 1994. The 1995 scale of the United Nations is adjusted by applying a mathematical coefficient to compensate for differences in membership between the Agency and the United Nations.
<P>
4. The calculations that were made in order to establish both the individual base rates and the resulting scale of assessment are reproduced for the information of the Conference in the Appendix.
<P>
5. Member States are urged to inform the Director General by 1 January 1996 as to when their Regular Budget contributions will be paid to the Agency. This information is required to enable the Secretariat to prepare cash forecasts on the basis of which the programme will be implemented.         
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A NAME=FOOTNOTE_1>         
<I>
See resolution GC(III)/RES/50, as amended by resolution GC(XXl)/RES/351.
</I>
</A>
<P>
<HR>
