<HEAD>
<TITLE>
YEARBOOK 1995
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<H2>
The IAEA Yearbook
</H2>
<P>
<B>
<!--plsfield:title-->
Part C:  Nuclear Power, Nuclear Fuel Cycle and Waste Management: Status
and Trends
</B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<!--plsfield:abstract-->
Part C of the IAEA Yearbook 1995 deals with the status and
trends in nuclear power, the nuclear fuel cycle and
radioactive waste management throughout the world, together
with a summary of the IAEA programmes in these areas.  Of
special note are the sections on recent changes in the uranium
market, the comparative assessment of the environmental
effects of nuclear and other energy sources and radioactive
waste management in central and eastern Europe.
<P>
<!--plsfield:content-->
<I>Contents:</I> Nuclear power; Nuclear fuel cycle;
Radioactive waste management.
<P>
<!--plsfield:reference-->
STI/PUB/987 (109 pp., 25 figures, 18 x 24 cm; 1995)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-101395-7
<BR>
<!--plsfield:price-->
Price:  200 Austrian Schillings
<!--
-end-><!-->
<P>
<HR>
<P>
