</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
YEARBOOK 1995
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<H2>
The IAEA Yearbook
</H2>
<P>
<B>
<!--plsfield:title-->
Part D:  Nuclear Safety Review 1995
</B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<!--plsfield:abstract-->
A new format has been adopted for the Nuclear Safety Review
1995.  The focus of the report has been shifted to feature a
number of prominent relevant issues and to concentrate on
their implications for radiation and nuclear safety.  It
includes in-depth discussion of steam generator integrity,
control rod drive nozzle cracking, fire protection, childhood
cancers near nuclear installations and radon induced health
effects.  Related IAEA activities such as the feedback of
operating experience based on the IAEA event reporting and
operational safety services are also addressed.
<P>
<!--plsfield:content-->
<I>Contents:</I> Highlights; Nuclear safety - topical issues;
Radiation safety - topical issues; International safety
activities.
<P>
<!--plsfield:reference-->
STI/PUB/988 (75 pp., 20 figures, 18 x 24 cm; 1995)
<BR>
ISBN 92-101495-3
<BR>
<!--plsfield:price-->
Price: 140 Austrian Schillings
<!--
-end-><!-->
<P>
