<HEAD>

<TITLE>Subject Scope</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Laura Roberson">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="../products.htm"><IMG SRC="../../graphic/prodserv.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>
<BR>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=6>Subject Scope</FONT> <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
The subject scope of INIS was developed to respond to the information
needs of the international community reflecting the IAEA's interests
and activities with regard to peaceful applications of nuclear
science and technology. Currently, INIS collects, processes and
disseminates information related to subjects as illustrated in
the following 1995 data:<BR>
<BR>
<TABLE BORDER=1> <TR><TD>Nuclear Power</TD><TD>20.5 %</TD> </TR><TR><TD>Fusion
Research and Technology</TD><TD>15.5 %</TD> </TR><TR><TD>Life
and Enviromental Sciences</TD><TD>14 %</TD> </TR><TR><TD>Nuclear
Materials</TD><TD>10.5 %</TD> </TR><TR><TD>Elementary Particles</TD><TD>10
%</TD> </TR><TR><TD>Nuclear Physics</TD><TD>7 %</TD> </TR><TR><TD>Chemistry</TD><TD>6
%</TD> </TR><TR><TD>Radioactive Waste</TD><TD>5.5 %</TD> </TR><TR><TD>Economic,
Legal, Social</TD><TD>5 %</TD> </TR><TR><TD>Earth Sciences</TD><TD>4
%</TD> </TR><TR><TD>Safeguards</TD><TD>1 %</TD> </TR><TR><TD>Isotopes</TD><TD>1
%</TD> </TR></TABLE><BR>
<BR>
<BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P>
