<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>INIS Online</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Stanik Zsolt">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="../products.htm"><IMG SRC="../../graphic/prodserv.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
 <FONT SIZE=6>Online Hosts</FONT> <BR>
<BR>
Authorized users may access the INIS Database through several
online hosts:
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>INIS ONLINE SERVICE OF THE IAEA</B> <BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
The INIS Database file online from the IAEA contains records from
1976 to the present. It is updated semi-monthly, with an average
annual increase of about 80,000 records. Information on access can be provided by your national <A HREF="../../liaison/liaison.htm">INIS Liaison Officer</A>
or by <A HREF="mailto:flory@nepo1.iaea.or.at">Ms R.Flory</A> in the INIS Section of the IAEA.
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
The INIS Database may be accessed online via the gateway to the
IAEA computer provided by the Information Retrieval of the European
Space Agency (ESA/IRS). ESA/IRS does not host INIS but does provide
its users with a gateway to the IAEA mainframe. <BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>INIS ONLINE THROUGH STN INTERNATIONAL</B> <BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
The INIS Database is maintained in the Fachinformationszentrum
(FIZ) Karlsruhe, Germany, and is accessible through STN International,
the Scientific and Technical Network, operated cooperatively by
FIZ Karlsruhe, the American Chemical Society (ACS) Columbus, Ohio
and the Japan Information Centre of Science and Technology (JICST),
Tokyo. The INIS file contains more than 1.8 million records from
1970 to the present. Requests for access to the INIS and/or Energy
Databases via STN International should be sent to one of the <A HREF="../stn.htm">STN Service Centers</A>.
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
INIS data are also available online as a part of the ENERGY Database
maintained by FIZ Karlsruhe. The ENERGY Database covers world-wide
literature on energy research and technology for all kinds of
energy sources including nuclear. It covers the period from 1974
to the present and contains more than 3.0 million records.

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Requests for access to the INIS and/or ENERGY Databases via STN
International should be sent to one of the <A HREF="../stn.htm">STN Service Centers</A>.

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>INIS ONLINE THROUGH DIALOG SERVICE</B> <BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
All member countries of the Energy Technology Data Exchange can
have access to INIS information online in the Energy Science and
Technology Database (INIS is included in the Database). The Database
covers the period from 1974 to the present. Requests for access
to the Energy Science and Technology Database (File 103) via DIALOG
Service should be sent to the <A HREF="../knight.htm">Knight-Ridder Offices</A>
around the world.

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>MEMBER COUNTRY ONLINE SERVICES</B> <BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Member countries also provide online access through national or
in-house systems designed to aid researchers and policy-makers.
In Japan, for instance, INIS data are available through an institutional
system in Japan Atomic Energy Research Institute (JAERI). In Belgium,
INIS data are available through the Belgian Information and Dissemination
Service (BELINDIS); in Brazil, from the Nuclear Information Centre.
Contact your country <A HREF="../../liaison/liaison.htm">Liaison Officer</A>
for information regarding online access to the INIS Database in
your country.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>



