<h2>Keep America Beautiful, Inc. Awards Programs</h2>
<blockquote>
    <p><a href="national.html"><strong>KAB's Annual National
    Awards Program</strong></a><br>
    KAB's annual awards program honoring citizen groups, schools,
    businesses, and government agencies.</p>
    <p><a href="ironeyes.html"><strong>Iron Eyes Cody Award/Mrs.
    Lyndon B. Johnson Award</strong></a><br>
    The Iron Eyes Cody Award honors outstanding volunteer men who
    have demonstrated lifelong leadership in raising public
    awareness about litter prevention, roadway and community
    beautification, the solid waste issue, and the need for
    citizens to participate in activities that preserve and
    enhance natural resources and public lands.</p>
    <p>The Mrs. Lyndon B. Johnson award honors outstanding
    volunteer women who throughout their life have focused their
    time and energy in making America a more beautiful country.</p>
    <p><a href="tca-awd.html"><strong>Take Care of America Awards</strong></a><br>
    Annual awards recognizing communities and groups for
    outstanding programs and/or projects that promote public
    lands stewardship and develop a sense of citizen ownership of
    local, state, and/or federal public lands and resources.</p>
    <p><a href="fhwa.html"><strong>FHWA/KAB Awards Program<br>
    </strong></a>Honors State Departments of Transportation for
    outstanding efforts within their communities. This awards
    program is co-sponsored by The Federal Highway Administration
    and Keep America Beautiful, Inc.</p>
    <p><a href="bab-awd.html"><strong>Build America Beautiful
    Awards Program<br>
    </strong></a>Recognizes builders participating in <a
    href="bab.html">Build America Beautiful</a> program from KAB
    and The National Association of Home Builders.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>If you have any questions about KAB's awards programs, please
see our <a href="staff.html">Staff Contact List</a> to find the
staff member who can best assist you.</p>
<hr>
<p>Return to <a href="index.html">Home Page</a>.</p>
