<html>
<head>
<title>Keep America Beautiful, Inc. - Catalog</title>
<meta name="KEYWORDS"
content="Keep America Beautiful, education, solid waste, litter prevention, composting, recycling, beautification">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p><!--Source code written by Dawn Rosner. FrontPage required for upload, and has tampered with the original coding--></p>
<p><img src="catlgbnr.gif" lowsrc="lctlgbnr.gif"
alt="KAB Catalog of Materials" align="bottom" width="531"
height="133"> </p>
<p><br>
Educating Americans of every age about solid waste, litter
prevention, and public lands stewardship has never been more
important. In partnership with national waste management experts,
educators, and membership of its National Advisory Council, Keep
America Beautiful, Inc. offers a variety of materials to meet
this need.</p>
<p>All items listed are with prices in U.S. Dollars. </p>
<p>Please call or write if you have a question about any of the
materials described.</p>
<hr>
<h3>Education</h3>
<dl>
    <dd><img src="curric.gif" lowsrc="lcurric.gif"
        alt="Curricula Guides" align="left" hspace="0"
        width="258" height="156"> </dd>
    <dt><a name="WIP"><strong>Waste in Place</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd>Curriculum for K-6 teachers. Features KAB Mascot Woody
        Woodpecker. Introduces students to litter and integrated
        solid waste management. 36 lesson plans grouped by
        subject, can be taught sequentially or individually.
        Promotes critical thinking and decision-making skills. <em>See </em><a
        href="teachers.html"><em>Material for Teachers</em></a><em>
        for additional information.</em></dd>
    <dd><a href="teachers.html">&#160;</a></dd>
    <dt><a name="WAHR"><strong>Waste: A Hidden Resource</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd>Curriculum for teachers in grades 7-12. An overview of
        solid waste and hazardous waste that encourages students'
        investigation and decision-making. &quot;Crisis in Center
        City&quot; involves students in role-playing to solve
        mock crisis. 36 free-standing lessons can be taught
        sequentially or individually. <em>See </em><a
        href="teachers.html"><em>Material for Teachers</em></a><em>
        for additional information. </em></dd>
    <dd><a href="teachers.html">&#160;</a></dd>
    <dt><a name="WIP"><strong>Plastics Recycling by the Numbers</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd><a name="WIP">Covers plastics' uses, the Plastic
        Container Coding system, and how to separate plastics for
        recycling. Grades 3-4. <em>50&#162;</em></a></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><a name="WIP"><strong>Mister Rogers' Activity Book for
        Young Children</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd><a name="WIP">Teaches children lessons on re-use and
        recycling. Has words and music to songs in companion
        video. <em>$1.50</em></a></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><a href="wwwht.html"><strong>Woody's Wise Waste Handling
        Tips for Kids</strong></a><br>
    </dt>
    <dd>Simple projects children can perform at home and in the
        classroom. First copy free, additional copies <em>20&#162;</em>.</dd>
</dl>
<hr>
<h3>Litter Prevention</h3>
<dl>
    <dt><a href="tips.html"><strong>Tips for Preventing Litter in
        Your Community</strong></a><br>
    </dt>
    <dd>Identifies behaviors causing littering, seven sources of
        litter, and provides ways to address the problem. First
        copy free, additional copies <em>20&#162;</em>.</dd>
</dl>
<hr>
