<hr>
<h3><a name="Scouts">Solid Waste</a> </h3>
<dl>
    <dt><a name="study"><strong>The Role of Recycling in
        Integrated Solid Waste Management to the Year 2000</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd><a name="study">KAB's comprehensive 1994 study on
        recycling and solid waste. For use by local solid waste
        decision-makers and officials as a tool for planning
        effective waste management. Also intended as a resource
        for libraries, schools, and government agencies. </a><a
        href="stdy-ful.html">25-page summary</a>, 206-page
        report, and 400 page appendices. <em>$71.00</em> </dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><a name="LoopKit"><strong>&quot;Close the Loop. Buy
        Recycled.&quot; Community Education Kit</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd><a name="LoopKit">Created by KAB and the U.S.
        Environmental Protection Agency, this kit allows your
        group or club to educate others about the importance of
        &quot;buying recycled.&quot; Can also be used by
        businesses, schools, and government agencies to educate
        employees. Includes manual, video, and camera-ready
        brochure. <em>$40.00.</em></a></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><a name="Overview"><strong>Overview of Municipal Solid
        Waste Management</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd><a name="Overview">Booklet provides general information
        on all options of solid waste disposal available in
        America today. <em>$5.00</em></a></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><a name="Overview"><strong>Waste in the Workplace</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd><a name="Overview">A guidebook to enable small businesses
        to minimize waste and lower disposal costs. A
        step-by-step approach that begins with a waste analysis.
        Offers ways to recycle and reduce commercial waste. <em>$4.50.</em></a></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><a name="Overview"><strong>What Can You Do? More Than You
        Think</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd><a name="Overview">A brochure about the solid waste
        issue. <em>First copy free, additional copies 25&#162;
        each.</em></a></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><a name="Overview"><strong>Household Appliances and the
        Environment</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd><a name="Overview">Resource guide and slide presentation
        covers household appliance recovery and related issues.
        Includes a camera-ready brochure to help raise public
        awareness. <em>$18.50</em></a></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><a name="Overview"><strong>Environmental Court Brochure</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd><a name="Overview">Provides a step-by-step process for
        establishing an environmental court. Prepared with the
        assistance of a panel of environmental court judges. <em>First
        copy free, additional copies 20&#162; each.</em></a></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><a name="Overview"><strong>Build America Beautiful
        Brochure</strong><br>
        </a></dt>
    <dd><a name="Overview">An excellent marketing tool which
        introduces the BAB program and includes an order form for
        a program media kit. <em>50&#162;</em></a></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><a href="mswfact.html"><strong>Focus Fact Sheet:
        Introduction to Municipal Solid Waste</strong></a><br>
    </dt>
    <dd>One page (2 sided) fact sheet of general information on
        municipal solid waste. <em>First copy free, additional
        copies 20&#162; each.</em></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><a href="tires.html"><strong>Focus Fact Sheet: Tire
        Recycling</strong></a><br>
    </dt>
    <dd>One page (2 sided) fact sheet of general information on
        tire recycling. <em>First copy free, additional copies
        20&#162; each.</em></dd>
</dl>
<hr>
<h3>Videos </h3>
<dl>
    <dt><strong>Environmental Court Video</strong><br>
    </dt>
    <dd>Explains the role and structure of an environmental
        court. Prepared by KAB state affiliate, Clean Tennessee,
        the University of Memphis and the Honorable Larry Potter
        for communities wanting to learn about environmental
        courts. One (1) complimentary environmental court
        planning guide brochure included. Length: 22:15 minutes. <em>$8.00</em> 
        <p><img src="rogers.gif" lowsrc="lrogers.gif"
        alt="Mr. Rogers' Recycling Video" align="right"
        hspace="0" width="200" height="210"> </p>
        <p><br>
        <br>
        <br>
        </p>
    </dd>
    <dt><strong>Mister Rogers' Recycling Video</strong><br>
    </dt>
    <dd>30-minute video produced by the acclaimed PBS series
        &quot;Mister Rogers' Neighborhood&quot; for children.
        Ideal for libraries and pre-schools. <em>$19.95</em> 
        <p><br>
        <br>
        <br>
        <br>
        </p>
    </dd>
    <dt><strong>Beyond the Bins&#151;Sustaining a Recycling
        Program in Your Community</strong><br>
    </dt>
    <dd>Describes steps in recycling beyond separation and put
        out by households. Covers programs set-up and hurdles. <em>$7.50</em></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><strong>How Did This Get Here?</strong><br>
    </dt>
    <dd>A 10-minute video to educate the public about litter and
        the adverse impacts that result when people mishandle
        waste. Identifies seven sources of litter and strategies
        to prevent it. <em>$8.00</em></dd>
    <dd>&#160;</dd>
    <dt><strong>Recycling Realities: A National Town Meeting</strong><br>
    </dt>
    <dd>A VHS tape of KAB's 1993 live interactive videoconference
        addressing the perceptions vs. realities of recycling and
        other options for community waste management. Emphasizing
        the integrated approach to managing waste. Length: 120
        minutes. <em>$20.00</em></dd>
</dl>
