<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3O/DTD HTML//EN">

<html>
<head>
<title>Keep America Beautiful, Inc. - Build America Beautiful</title>
<meta name="KEYWORDS"
content="Build America Beautiful, Keep America Beautiful, KAB, BAB, construction, litter, beautification">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p><!--Source code written by Dawn Rosner. FrontPage required for upload, and has tampered with the original coding--></p>
<p><img src="babbnr.gif" lowsrc="lbabbnr.gif"
alt="Keep America Beautiful - Build America Beautiful"
align="bottom" width="531" height="133"> <img src="bab.gif"
lowsrc="lbab.gif" alt="Build America Beautiful logo" align="left"
hspace="0" width="258" height="272"></p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
Build America Beautiful is an entirely voluntary program
developed in partnership between the National Association of Home
Builders (NAHB) and Keep America Beautiful, Inc. The program is
sponsored nationally by Amoco Chemicals, The Home Depot and Home
&amp; Garden TV Network. Build America Beautiful is all about
doing some simple things that will help you as well as your
employees and subcontractors become more aware about the litter
created around job sites and take better care to see that the
waste we do create gets handled properly.</p>
<p><br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<h3>More Than Just A Pretty Site</h3>
<p>Builders who have taken part in Build America Beautiful report
that keeping a close eye on waste and litter around their sites
actually made the sites safer and reduced potential liability. It
increased the marketability of their work during and after
construction and boosted employee morale on-site. Even better, it
cemented their ongoing relationships with the community.</p>
<p><br>
<br>
</p>
<h3>It's Easy!</h3>
<p>It's easy to participate. Just follow the easy-to-use <a
href="babguide.html">guidelines</a> laid out in detail for you in
the Build America Beautiful Membership Kit. Along with the
guidelines, you'll be gaining a wealth of ready-to-use tools for
building America beautiful including ad-slicks of the Build
America Beautiful logo which you can use in your own advertising,
a sample press release for announcing your involvement, site
decals, hard hat stickers and the Construction Site Recycling
Handbook. </p>
<p>By taking part in Build America Beautiful, you'll also make
yourself eligible for an annual national awards program
recognizing America's most beautiful builders. <a
href="bab-awd.html">Entry forms</a> are available from NAHB and
Keep America Beautiful, Inc.</p>
<p><br>
<br>
</p>
<h3>What Are You Waiting For?</h3>
<p>Join the team that's building with pride and keeping America
beautiful. Call NAHB toll-free at 1-800-223-2665 to have your
Build America Beautiful membership kit shipped out today. You'll
become part of a nationwide solution that can do good things for
your community and great things for your business. Now that's a
winning combination!</p>
<hr>
<p>Return to <a href="partner.html">National Partnerships</a>.</p>
<p>Return to <a href="index.html">Home Page</a>.</p>
