<head>
<title>Keep America Beautiful, Inc. - GLAD Bag-A-Thon&#174;</title>
<meta name="KEYWORDS"
content="Keep America Beautiful, GLAD, Bag-A-Thon, cleanup, litter, recycling, beautification">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p><!--Source code written by Dawn Rosner. FrontPage required for upload, and has tampered with the original coding--></p>
<p><img src="gladbnr.gif" lowsrc="lgladbnr.gif"
alt="Keep America Beautiful - GLAD Bag-A-Thon&#174;"
align="bottom" width="531" height="133"> </p>
<p><img src="glad.gif" lowsrc="lglad.gif"
alt="GLAD Bag-A-Thon&#174; Logo" align="right" hspace="0"
width="234" height="237"> </p>
<p>The GLAD Bag-A-Thon&#174; program, a partnership between Keep
America Beautiful, Inc. (KAB) and First Brands Corporation, is
the largest organized cleanup and recycling effort in the nation.
Since 1986, when the Bag-A-Thon&#174; program was piloted in five
KAB Affiliate communities, the program has continued to grow
successfully. Since 1990, the program has included more than 100
cities/communities nationwide. </p>
<p>The program promotes proper waste handling practices by
encouraging Americans to help clean up and restore neglected
public lands into usable space, recycle materials to preserve the
nation's resources and reuse clothing to help the needy and
divert it from landfills. </p>
<p>Bag-A-Thon&#174; volunteers learn their responsibility for
proper waste handling by cleaning up littered parks, beaches,
streets and neighborhoods and going a step further by restoring
neglected parks, illegal dumpsites and littered thoroughfares and
public facilities. In many cities, volunteers also participate in
organized multi-material recycling drives and/or clothing drives. </p>
<p>GLAD Wrap and Bags supports the program with the donation of
Handle-Tie Trash and Recycling Bags as well as educational
brochures about proper waste handling practices and provides
ongoing assistance to its Bag-A-Thon&#174; partner communities in
organizing the programs and obtaining widespread awareness for
local efforts. </p>
<p>For additional information on the GLAD Bag-A-Thon&#174;
program, call 1-800-262-GLAD, or <a
href="mailto:keepamerbe@aol.com">e-mail our staff</a>. </p>
<hr>
<p>Return to <a href="partner.html">National Partnerships</a>.</p>
<p>Return to <a href="index.html">Home Page</a>.</p>
