<html>
<head>
<title>Keep America Beautiful, Inc. - &quot;Close the Loop. Buy
Recycled.&quot;</title>
<meta name="KEYWORDS"
content="Keep America Beautiful, Close the Loop, Buy Recycled, KAB, recycling">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p><!--Source code written by Dawn Rosner. FrontPage required for upload, and has tampered with the original coding--></p>
<p><img src="loopbnr.gif" lowsrc="lloopbnr.gif"
alt="Keep America Beautiful - Close the Loop.  Buy Recycled."
align="bottom" width="531" height="133"> </p>
<p><img src="loop.gif" lowsrc="lloop.gif"
alt="Close the Loop.  Buy Recycled." align="right" hspace="0"
width="398" height="182">In a two-year partnership between Keep
America Beautiful, Inc. (KAB) and the U.S. Environmental
Protection Agency (EPA), a number of KAB community affiliates
developed and field-tested strategies for increasing awareness of
buying recycled. From their programs, the &quot;Close the Loop.
Buy Recycled.&quot; Community Education Kit was developed.</p>
<p>The kit's proven strategies have been used by Keep America
Beautiful affiliates nationwide to increase purchases of recycled
goods by consumers and businesses. Here are just a few ideas
implemented by KAB affiliate pilot projects through use of the
kit:</p>
<ul type="disc">
    <li>A coalition of 100 concerned business leaders and
        government officials was formed.</li>
    <li>A procurement policy was adopted to promote an effort to
        establish and implement city-wide buy-recycled practices.</li>
    <li>A half-day seminar was conducted titled, &quot;How
        Recycling Can Effect Your Bottom Line.&quot;</li>
    <li>Treasure hunts were conducted at a local mall to identify
        products made with recycled materials.</li>
    <li>Awards programs were established to recognize businesses
        and institutions which practiced buying recycled or
        helped educate the public about &quot;closing the
        loop.&quot; </li>
</ul>
<p><br>
<br>
The &quot;Close the Loop. Buy Recycled.&quot; Community Education
Kit tools include:</p>
<blockquote>
    <p>Manual with step-by-step guide to awareness campaigns </p>
    <p>Camera-ready brochure for recycling centers or events </p>
    <p>Print and radio public service announcements </p>
    <p>Educational video featuring EPA Administrator Carol
    Browner </p>
</blockquote>
<p><br>
<br>
To order a &quot;Close the Loop. Buy Recycled.&quot; kit, please
see our <a href="stuff.html#LoopKit">catalog</a>.</p>
<hr>
<p>Return to <a href="partner.html">National Partnerships</a>.</p>
<p>Return to <a href="index.html">Home Page</a>.</p>
